TopicTitle: What Have I Found Near Gilly?

Articles.Content:
I was recently flying past Gilly on a failed attempt to gain science when I saw this:

http://i.imgur.com/BhgmIUX.png

I managed to position the window of my pod to face the object that looked a bit like a fuel tank.

I would really like some insight as to what this might be.

P.S I am new, so if I posted this thread in the wrong place, let me know.

Looks like an SRB model.

Otherwise, a swarm of interplanetary Whack-A-Kerbal spheroids?

Well... I'm stumped

They kinda look like the spheres Danny2726 spawns in this:
Yep, looks like wack a kerbal to me.
Yeah, it's the balls from the cheat Whack-a-kerbal.
Looks like a long range shot of a stack of Rockomax 32 tanks. Perhaps 16s?

Looks like a long range shot of a stack of Rockomax 32 tanks. Perhaps 16s?

If you zoom in, its pretty clearly a chain of spheres, not a cylinder

The post that launched a thousand ships... all heading for Eve

My up coming mission there just gained a new objective.

Whack-a-kerbal, I've made that same mistake thinking they're (the whack-a-kerbal objects) an easter egg before...

Whack-a-kerbal, I've made that same mistake thinking it's an easter egg before...

Well, IIRC, whackakerbal balls despawn after exiting physics range, rather than saving as objects, so why is there a dozen of them lying in a crater on Gilly?

Time to construct a second Sentari tour ship as the first is in transit right now.
It might be a warning from eve since it look kinda like a '!'

I feel a bit stupid now.
Lol, this mission is a failure, but I'm not sure a planet can predict that!
